  "body": "We should note in the README for our  TypeScript projects that clients may need to enable `skipLibCheck` setting in their `tsconfig.json` to avoid issues similar to that discovered in PR #4719. Truffle has a number of TypeScript projects that should be checked to see if the note is necessary. See list below\r\n\r\n## How to check\r\n\r\nNote, there may be a quicker way... ask in #engineering\r\n\r\n1. create a typescript project\r\n2. add one of the projects below as the sole dependency\r\n3. create a source file with only `import xxx from @truffle/package`\r\n4. run tsc \r\n  - compiles ok, all is good!\r\n   - fails to compile? Determine if enabling `skipLibCheck`  resolves the problem\r\n\r\n\r\n## Typescript packages\r\n- [ ] abi-utils\r\n- [ ] artifactor\r\n- [ ] blockchain-utils\r\n- [ ] box\r\n- [ ] code-utils\r\n- [ ] codec/docs\r\n- [ ] codec\r\n- [ ] compile-common\r\n- [ ] compile-solidity\r\n- [ ] config\r\n- [ ] db\r\n- [ ] db-kit\r\n- [ ] db-loader\r\n- [ ] decoder\r\n- [ ] error\r\n- [ ] expect\r\n- [ ] fetch-and-compile\r\n- [ ] hdwallet-provider\r\n- [ ] interface-adapter\r\n- [ ] plugins\r\n- [ ] preserve/docs\r\n- [ ] preserve\r\n- [ ] preserve-fs\r\n- [ ] preserve-to-buckets\r\n- [ ] preserve-to-filecoin\r\n- [ ] preserve-to-ipfs\r\n- [ ] profiler\r\n- [ ] provisioner\r\n- [ ] resolver\r\n- [ ] source-fetcher\r\n",
